Standard and Poor's Corp said itaffirmed about 600 mln dlrs of debt of Republic Bank NY Corp.    Affirmed were Republic's AA senior debt, AA-minussubordinated debt, A-plus preferred stock, A-1-plus commercialpaper and A/A-1-plus certificates of deposit.    S and P cited the bank's decision to join the growingnumber of U.S. banks that have set aside reserves fordeveloping country credits.    Republic strengthed its reserves by 100 mln dlrs.    Despite an expected second quarter loss, the firm remainsone of the best capitalized banks in the U.S., S and P said. Reuter&#3;